{"id": "1409531326905974867", "channel_id": "1409531326905974867", "type": 0, "author_id": "292999814558515200", "author_name": "_wickedcat_", "author_bot": false, "content": "What I mean is when you read the card and it generates another card you can see said card in the description but if that other card creates more cards or keywords you can't see them- Sounds rediculous but it is quite the problem on characters like Hameln or Myriam who generate a lot of consecutive stuff. For example Hameln generates \"Symphony of Harmony\" that generates \"Ascending Scale\" or \"Descending scale\" and there is no way that I know of to read what they do without actually going into a game and using the card which is quite an ordeal to just read what cards do. Doesn't need to be a hard fix either, you can just add the generated cards as extra descriptions on the same screen", "timestamp": "2025-08-25T13:34:16.160000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 3}], "attachments": [{"id": "1409531327442849863", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 1650245, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1409531326905974867/1409531327442849863/image.png?ex=69cbcd58&is=69ca7bd8&hm=caa05736631e74351737c38998f6c4e191dc8a627010f2cc7b04aaced69adca3&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1409531326905974867", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Suggestion: See cards in descriptions of cards", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
